Copayments or similar charges shall not be imposed for the following services:
All services provided to children under eighteen (18) years of age;
All services furnished to pregnant women, if the services relate to the pregnancy or to any other medical condition which may complicate the pregnancy;
Emergency services including hospital, clinic, office, or other facility services which are necessary to prevent the death or serious impairment of the individual;
Services furnished to institutionalized individuals if the individual is required, as a condition of receiving services, to spend all but a minimal amount of income for personal needs;
Services furnished for an individual who is receiving hospice care as defined under Section 1905 of Title XIX of the Federal Social Security Act, 42 U.S.C. sec. 1396d(o); and
Other services excluded from cost sharing by federal law or regulation.
